Agreement

 

EUSA Pharma – COVID-19 Guidelines  

 

EUSA Pharma cares about the health and wellbeing of its employees. Over the last few months, we have implemented a number of measures which have been aligned with government guidance as a minimum to ensure your safety, whilst also providing employees with as much flexibility as possible in the current environment.    

 

However, these are unconventional times and we have to adapt to our changing environment. Following the Government announcement on Monday 4th January 2021 of the National Lockdown and the alarming spread of the virus, particularly in Hertfordshire and surrounding areas, we would like to update you with the latest guidance for both our office based and field based employees to ensure full clarity on the company’s position in light of government advice – both your health and safety, as well as our responsibility to the wider community are our first priority. 

 

The office will remain open, however, at a reduced capacity. This means a maximum of 2 people in the Third Floor Office and a maximum of 1 person in the Ground Floor Office, and only for those that absolutely cannot work from home. Cannot work from home may include an adverse home working event (eg. no internet) or business critical activities (eg. high volume of printing, IT equipment access, opening post etc). Only come in if it is absolutely necessary 

 

Our hot desk system will remain in place. Anybody intending to come into the office, must use our desk booking app https://eusahotdeskbooking.azurewebsites.net/. We have linked up the Hot-Desk Booking System with the security system on our EUSA Pharma Office Doors, which restricts access to only those who have booked a desk in advance. Even if you are only popping into the office for a short visit and don’t need a desk, you must book using the app. 

 

Whilst in the Office and Breakspear Park, please also ensure you follow all Government guidelines. It is imperative that you maintain social distancing of at least 2 metres to ensure the safety of yourself and others. For all up to date government guidelines, please visit the Government website: https://www.gov.uk/coronavirus 

 

The company’s stance remains the same with face to face meetings. We do not support face to face meetings at this time.  

 

For those Field-based employees, Jon Sayers and Ollie will continue to provide you with guidance.  

 

If you have any concerns about working from home and you do not feel comfortable talking to your manager, please reach out to Lucy Bourne or Emma Maggot from our HR team. They will provide you with individual support to talk through your concerns and to help find the right solution for you. Our Employee Assistance Programme also provides independent advice and support and more details can be found on their leaflet, on their website www.myemployeecare.com or contact 0800 917 9330.  

 

The Covid-19 environment is unpredictable, which means we will continue to monitor the effectiveness of the measures we have put in place, government advice and local restrictions and will revise our guidelines accordingly.  

 

Prior to office visits: 

 

Do NOT come into the office if: 

  • You are feeling unwell on the day or if you have a temperature. We recommend whenever feasible, that you do check your temperature prior to coming into the office.  

  • If you have experienced any COVID-19 symptoms in the previous 7 days 

  • Have been in close contact with anyone with a confirmed case of COVID-19 in the last 14 days 

  • Have travelled to any country within the previous 14 days that is not a government-approved travel corridor https://www.gov.uk/guidance/coronavirus-covid-19-travel-corridors 

 

By agreeing to these guidelines, if you are tested positive for COVID-19 after working in the office, you must immediately contact your line manager or a member of the HR team to inform them. We will then contact those that were in the office at the same time and advise that there has been a confirmed positive case.  

 

In the Office: 

 

A Hot Desk must be booked prior to your office visit. You must not come to the office without a booking.  

 

Please be aware that the back entrances to the building are closed. You must enter the building through main reception and sign in and out with the Security team at Reception.  

 

Signage 

  • Signage has been displayed throughout the offices, highlighting the actions all employees need to take in order to keep themselves and colleagues safe.   Please observe these instructions at all times whilst in the office and in Breakspear Park.  

 

PPE & Cleaning products 

  • You are required to wear a face mask when moving through the main office areas. You do not have to wear a mask whilst working from a desk or when seated in a meeting room. 

  • We ask that if you are in the office and seated at your desk and somebody approaches to speak to you, that you please ensure you put on your face mask immediately 

  • Masks and gloves have been provided at every entry point into the office. Please help yourself to these whilst you are in the office if you do not have your own mask.  

  • You must sanitise your hands on entering the office. 

  • You must sanitise your hands prior to touching any equipment in the main office area.  

  • Please ensure you wipe down frequent touch points before and after use. Frequent Touch Points include: Door handles, printers, cupboards, light switches, meeting room equipment and tables, booking systems, desk equipment, kitchen equipment  

  • We recommend that you sanitise and wash your hands regularly 

  • In the coming weeks, we will have non-contact temperature checkers which you can use at your own discretion and you will not be required to disclose any readings, but we encourage you to use them and help keep others safe. These will be located by all EUSA Office Entrances.  

 

Hotdesking  

  • EUSA will be operating a hotdesking policy of one person per desk per day. 

  • A maximum of 2 desks will be bookable in the Third Floor Office and a maximum of 1 desk will be bookable in the Ground Floor Office.  

  • The Third Floor Office will be split into ‘Side A’ and ‘Side B’ (Please see diagram below), to ensure there is a safe distance between employees at all times.  

  • Each employee will need to book either ‘Side A’ or ‘Side B’ on the booking system. The employee will be able to sit at any desk within their Side.   

  • In the Ground Floor Office, Employees will be able to sit at any desk. 

  • At the end of each day, please could you collect a ‘Desk Used’ sign from the PPE stations and leave this on the desk which you have been using, so that the cleaners can ensure they carry out a thorough clean on this desk.  

  • EUSA has worked closely with the Design Team at Morgan Lovell who have reviewed our office space and have advised us of the changes required to suit government guidelines, whilst also creating a safe environment for our employees and maintaining a productive workspace. 

  • All desks and all equipment on the desks will be disinfected by the cleaner on a daily basis, but we ask that you please clean all desks and equipment again with the Dettol wipes provided, before and after use.  

  • Desk phones are out of use, so please use your mobile phones to make any calls.  

  • If you are seated at your desk and somebody approaches to speak to you, please ensure you put on your mask. 

  • If you have booked a desk but have decided not to come in, please ensure you cancel your desk booking to enable others to come into the office. 

  • For more details on how to book a desk, please see below:  

 

 

App - EUSA Office Bookings 

  • How to book a desk: 

  • To book a desk, please follow the link below to the EUSA Office Bookings App: 

  • Link: https://eusahotdeskbooking.azurewebsites.net/ 

  • Desks will be available to book, up to 2 weeks in advance.   

  • On this app, you will be able to view all your desk bookings. You will also be able to inform your colleague of the days you have booked to come into the office as well as which desk you have booked.    

  • If you have booked a desk but have decided not to come in, please ensure you cancel your booking to enable others to come into the office.  

 

Meeting Rooms 

  • Due to the company’s updated position on meetings, the meeting rooms may only available for single person usage until such time as restrictions can be lifted.  

  • Once seated in the meeting room, you may remove your mask as long as the door is kept closed.  

  • Do not move the chairs out of the seating zones as they are there for a reason! 

  • At the end of each day, please could you collect a ‘Desk Used’ sign from the PPE stations and leave this on the meeting room table which you have been using, so that the cleaners can ensure they carry out a thorough clean in this area.  

  • If you would like to use the Flipcharts/whiteboards, please ensure you wipe down the pens with the Dettol wipes provided and sanitise your hands before and after use.  

  • Please ensure telephones are used on handsfree only 

  • Please ensure that you wipe down frequent touchpoints in the meeting rooms before and after use, and please sanitise your hands regularly.  

  • Frequent touchpoints: Desk areas, chair armrests, door handles, iPads, telephones, light switches, heating dials, flipchart pens  

 

  • Meeting Room Capacities:  

  • All meeting rooms have a capacity of 1 at this time 

 

How to book a meeting room: 

  • Please go to your Outlook calendar to book a meeting room.  

  • Please remember the maximum capacity for each meeting room is 1 

 

Communal Areas 

  • Please be vigilant and aware of others (employees and service providers) when moving around the office and building 

  • When moving around the office and going to meeting rooms, please follow the main walkways and avoid walking through desk areas where possible.  

  • A one-way system has been created around the cupboards located near the stationary room and kitchen in the Third Floor Office. Another one-way system has also been created around the cupboards located by the entrance of the Ground Floor Office.  

  • As we are unable to create a one-way system throughout the whole of the office, we have created “laybys” to enable people to maintain social distancing. Please be prepared in all instances to move in order to create a safer distance between yourself and other, utilising laybys and extra space.  

  • Please wear your face masks at all times when moving around the office area  

  • If you are seated at your desk and somebody approaches to speak to you, please ensure you put on your mask.  

  • We recommend that you print, copy and scan in bulk, to reduce the number of times at the printer. Please do not queue at the printer station. If the printer is being used by another colleague, please come back later.  

  • First aid kits are located in the kitchen in the Third Floor Office and in the reception area of the ground floor office. 

  • The collaboration area in the centre of the Third Floor Office will be closed  

  • The High Lunch table in the Ground Floor Office will be out of use  

  • A maximum of one person can enter the post/stationary room in the Third Floor Office 

  • Some Service Providers may be on site during the working day. All service providers are aware of EUSA’s COVID Guidelines and will abide by their company and EUSA’s rule and regulations. Please ensure you are aware of service providers when they are moving through the offices.  

 

Kitchen: 

  • The Kitchens in both offices will be open. Please only use on an essential needs basis, especially if you are seated in Side A, as you will need to move through Side B in order to access it.  

  • Lunch can be eaten at your desks or at the outside seating areas in Breakspear Park. Do not use the tables in the Kitchen at this time. 

  • The Maximum number of people in each kitchen at any one time are as follows: 

  • Third Floor Kitchen – Maximum of 1 person in the Kitchen area. The Third Floor Office Lunch Tables/Seating areas are closed.  

  • Ground Floor Office – Maximum of 1 person in the kitchen area. The Ground Floor Lunch Table is closed and the seating area in the Kitchen is out of use.  

  • EUSA has supplied individual teabags, coffee and sugar sachets to reduce touchpoints  

  • The Nespresso machines in both office and the Main Coffee Machine in the Third Floor Office will be out of use. Please use the sachets instead.  

  • The Kettles, Microwaves and toasters will be available for employees to use. As these are frequent touchpoints, please ensure that you clean this equipment before and after using the Dettol wipes provided and ensure you sanitise your hand before and after use. 

  • Cups, plates cutlery etc. are available and will be cleaned in the dishwasher, but please feel free to bring your own if you prefer. Disposable paper cups are available.  

  • Please fill up the dishwasher with used kitchen equipment. Please wash or sanitise your hands before and after using the dishwasher 

  • Frequent touchpoints: Microwave, kettle, toaster, cupboard handles, taps, water machine, milk bottles etc. Please clean these touchpoints with Dettol wipes before and after use and please sanitise your hands before and after use.  

  • The Table tennis and Pool Table in the Third Floor Office will be out of use.  

 

Visitors 

  • External visitors are not authorised to enter EUSA premises.  

 

Working Hours 

  • The offices will be open to employees between 08:00 – 17:30.  

  • Employees must leave the offices by 17:30, to allow the service providers to access the offices and carry out works after working hours  

 

Dress Code 

  • Friday dress code will be in place during this period  

 

Breakspear Park Facilities: 

  • Should there be any facility issues within Breakspear Park (e.g. Air Con, Heating, toilets, power outage etc) please contact one of the admin team (Miriam, Lorraine, Felicity or Megan) who will liaise directly with the Breakspear Park Maintenance Team to resolve any issues. 

 

Adherence to the Guidelines 

  • By reading and accepting these guidelines you are agreeing to observe all instructions and restrictions put in place, including the wearing of a face mask in open areas 

  • Failing to observe these guidelines will results in disciplinary action 

  • If you witness somebody failing to observe the guidelines, or acting in a way that is unsafe, please escalate to your line manager or a member of HR. If you are not comfortable with coming forward and wish to remain anonymous, we would encourage you to please visit our confidential ethics reporting site at https://secure.ethicspoint.eu, which is hosted by a third party called EthicsPoint. Here you will find more information on how you can submit an anonymous report either in writing or by telephone. 

 

In case of emergency 

  • If the fire alarm goes off, you should follow normal procedure (please see guidance from Breakspear Park) 

  • In case of a medical emergency, you should seek help and/or call 999. A trained EUSA First aider will be on site.

Breakspear Park – Return to the Office Guidelines 

 

Breakspear Park have created a guideline document, which you will find together with this document. However, please find below some key points.  

 

Signing in and out 

  • All employees must report to Reception on arrival and on departure, to sign in and out at with the security team  

 

Signage and PPE 

  • Breakspear Park strongly recommend that face coverings are worn whilst moving around common areas within the building, unless you are exempt in doing so.  

  • Breakspear Park have displayed Signage throughout the building, highlighting actions employees need to take to keep themselves and others safe. 

  • Touch free Hand Sanitisers have been placed by entrances and exits to the building as well as by the lifts.  

Toilets 

  • A maximum of two people in the toilets at any one time. 

  • The middle taps and cubicles are out of use to follow social distancing guidelines 

  • Breakspear Park ask that the inner door remains open, where possible to allow users to easily see if someone is in the area or leaving  

 

Café and Restaurant 

  • The Starbucks Café is now open  

  • The Restaurant remains closed  

 

Lifts and Stairs  

  • Breakspear Park are operating a one-person policy for all lifts in the building 

  • Breakspear Park are operating a one-way system on the staircases. Please see directions below: 

Please note: In the event of an emergency, this procedure would be overruled, and all staff should exit via their nearest fire exit
